      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09B\",\"process_rule\":\"1. **Copy decision table into table J09B_temp where the tour starts with J09B.**\\n2. **Add ENTSCHEIDUNG column.**\\n3. **Classify meter reading type:** Apply decision logic to set `ENTSCHEIDUNG`:\\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to \\\"KSA\\\" when a HAUS has less than 3 EQUNR.\\n   - ELSE set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to \\\"EVU\\\".\\n   - SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \\\"EVU\\\".\\n   - SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 500 - 599 to \\\"EVU\\\".\\n   - SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 900 - 999 to \\\"EVU\\\".\\n4. **JOIN table with EABLG table using INSTALLATION.**\\n5. **JOIN table with SALES_MASTER and NET_MASTER table using EQUNR.**\\n6. **Compare customer sales master data and net master data.**\\n7. **Decision: Check if sales customer data is NOT empty.**\\n   - **If True:** Use sales customer data table entries.\\n   - **Else:** Use net data customer table entries.\\n8. **Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09B** using column names: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n9. **Send email with the CSV file to EVU.**\\n   - Email address: meter.readings@evu.com\\n   - File path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>\\n10. **Delete temporary table.**\"}",
            "id": "lc_af6dd8eb-9128-4f9b-9db8-add622aa681c"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "b15750e7-a19a-4061-8024-9c9e33537df3",
        "tool_call_id": "call_h6nc7vw8",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09B",
            "process_rule": "1. **Copy decision table into table J09B_temp where the tour starts with J09B.**\n2. **Add ENTSCHEIDUNG column.**\n3. **Classify meter reading type:** Apply decision logic to set `ENTSCHEIDUNG`:\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to \"KSA\" when a HAUS has less than 3 EQUNR.\n   - ELSE set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to \"EVU\".\n   - SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \"EVU\".\n   - SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 500 - 599 to \"EVU\".\n   - SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 900 - 999 to \"EVU\".\n4. **JOIN table with EABLG table using INSTALLATION.**\n5. **JOIN table with SALES_MASTER and NET_MASTER table using EQUNR.**\n6. **Compare customer sales master data and net master data.**\n7. **Decision: Check if sales customer data is NOT empty.**\n   - **If True:** Use sales customer data table entries.\n   - **Else:** Use net data customer table entries.\n8. **Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09B** using column names: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n9. **Send email with the CSV file to EVU.**\n   - Email address: meter.readings@evu.com\n   - File path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>\n10. **Delete temporary table.**"
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
